{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":634,"text":"Philosophers, dramatists, theologians"},{"time":4214,"text":"have grappled with\nthis question for centuries:"},{"time":6444,"text":"what makes people go wrong?"},{"time":8000,"text":"Interestingly, I asked this question\nwhen I was a little kid."},{"time":11000,"text":"I grew up in the South Bronx,\ninner-city ghetto in New York,"},{"time":14080,"text":"and I was surrounded by evil,"},{"time":15587,"text":"as all kids are who grew up\nin an inner city."},{"time":18167,"text":"And I had friends\nwho were really good kids,"},{"time":20516,"text":"who lived out the Dr. Jekyll Mr. Hyde\nscenario -- Robert Louis Stevenson."},{"time":24832,"text":"That is, they took drugs,\ngot in trouble, went to jail."},{"time":28000,"text":"Some got killed, and some did it\nwithout drug assistance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32288,"text":"So when I read Robert Louis Stevenson,\nthat wasn't fiction."},{"time":35106,"text":"The only question is,\nwhat was in the juice?"},{"time":37354,"text":"And more importantly, that line\nbetween good and evil --"},{"time":41000,"text":"which privileged people like to think\nis fixed and impermeable,"},{"time":44492,"text":"with them on the good side,\nthe others on the bad side --"},{"time":47189,"text":"I knew that line was movable,\nand it was permeable."},{"time":50276,"text":"Good people could be\nseduced across that line,"},{"time":52643,"text":"and under good and some rare\ncircumstances, bad kids could recover"},{"time":56871,"text":"with help, with reform,\nwith rehabilitation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"So I want to begin\nwith this wonderful illusion"},{"time":62501,"text":"by [Dutch] artist M.C. Escher."},{"time":64799,"text":"If you look at it and focus on the white,\nwhat you see is a world full of angels."},{"time":68684,"text":"But let's look more deeply, and as we do,"},{"time":71276,"text":"what appears is the demons,\nthe devils in the world."},{"time":74832,"text":"That tells us several things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76237,"text":"One, the world is, was, will always\nbe filled with good and evil,"},{"time":79369,"text":"because good and evil is the yin and yang\nof the human condition."},{"time":82441,"text":"It tells me something else."},{"time":83751,"text":"If you remember,\nGod's favorite angel was Lucifer."},{"time":87289,"text":"Apparently, Lucifer means \"the light.\""},{"time":89751,"text":"It also means \"the morning star,\"\nin some scripture."},{"time":92501,"text":"And apparently, he disobeyed God,"},{"time":95730,"text":"and that's the ultimate\ndisobedience to authority."},{"time":98246,"text":"And when he did, Michael, the archangel,\nwas sent to kick him out of heaven"},{"time":103768,"text":"along with the other fallen angels."},{"time":105795,"text":"And so Lucifer descends into hell,\nbecomes Satan,"},{"time":109000,"text":"becomes the devil, and the force\nof evil in the universe begins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112024,"text":"Paradoxically, it was God\nwho created hell as a place to store evil."},{"time":116976,"text":"He didn't do a good job\nof keeping it there though."},{"time":119381,"text":"So, this arc of the cosmic transformation\nof God's favorite angel into the Devil,"},{"time":123994,"text":"for me, sets the context\nfor understanding human beings"},{"time":127662,"text":"who are transformed from good,\nordinary people into perpetrators of evil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132577,"text":"So the Lucifer effect,\nalthough it focuses on the negatives --"},{"time":136628,"text":"the negatives that people can become,"},{"time":139307,"text":"not the negatives that people are --"},{"time":141293,"text":"leads me to a psychological definition."},{"time":144671,"text":"Evil is the exercise of power."},{"time":146668,"text":"And that's the key: it's about power."},{"time":148931,"text":"To intentionally harm\npeople psychologically,"},{"time":151520,"text":"to hurt people physically,\nto destroy people mortally, or ideas,"},{"time":155274,"text":"and to commit crimes against humanity."},{"time":159000,"text":"If you Google \"evil,\" a word that should\nsurely have withered by now,"},{"time":162310,"text":"you come up with 136 million hits\nin a third of a second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"A few years ago -- I am sure\nall of you were shocked, as I was,"},{"time":170522,"text":"with the revelation of American soldiers\nabusing prisoners in a strange place"},{"time":176000,"text":"in a controversial war,\nAbu Ghraib in Iraq."},{"time":179000,"text":"And these were men and women"},{"time":181031,"text":"who were putting prisoners\nthrough unbelievable humiliation."},{"time":185976,"text":"I was shocked, but I wasn't surprised,"},{"time":187810,"text":"because I had seen\nthose same visual parallels"},{"time":190000,"text":"when I was the prison superintendent\nof the Stanford Prison Study."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193426,"text":"Immediately the Bush\nadministration military said what?"},{"time":196521,"text":"What all administrations say\nwhen there's a scandal:"},{"time":199045,"text":"\"Don't blame us. It's not the system."},{"time":200919,"text":"It's the few bad apples,\nthe few rogue soldiers.\""},{"time":203343,"text":"My hypothesis is,\nAmerican soldiers are good, usually."},{"time":206398,"text":"Maybe it was the barrel that was bad."},{"time":208483,"text":"But how am I going to deal\nwith that hypothesis?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"I became an expert witness\nfor one of the guards,"},{"time":213544,"text":"Sergeant Chip Frederick,\nand in that position,"},{"time":215711,"text":"I had access to the dozen\ninvestigative reports."},{"time":218648,"text":"I had access to him."},{"time":220472,"text":"I could study him, have him come\nto my home, get to know him,"},{"time":223797,"text":"do psychological analysis to see,\nwas he a good apple or bad apple."},{"time":227228,"text":"And thirdly, I had access\nto all of the 1,000 pictures"},{"time":231163,"text":"that these soldiers took."},{"time":232865,"text":"These pictures are\nof a violent or sexual nature."},{"time":235399,"text":"All of them come from the cameras\nof American soldiers."},{"time":238809,"text":"Because everybody has\na digital camera or cell phone camera,"},{"time":241692,"text":"they took pictures of everything,\nmore than 1,000."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244050,"text":"And what I've done is I organized them\ninto various categories."},{"time":247028,"text":"But these are by United States\nmilitary police, army reservists."},{"time":252477,"text":"They are not soldiers prepared\nfor this mission at all."},{"time":255983,"text":"And it all happened in a single place,\nTier 1-A, on the night shift."},{"time":259680,"text":"Why?"},{"time":260905,"text":"Tier 1-A was the center\nfor military intelligence."},{"time":263531,"text":"It was the interrogation hold."},{"time":265531,"text":"The CIA was there."},{"time":266756,"text":"Interrogators from\nTitan Corporation, all there,"},{"time":269938,"text":"and they're getting no information\nabout the insurgency."},{"time":272748,"text":"So they're going to put pressure\non these soldiers,"},{"time":275242,"text":"military police, to cross the line,"},{"time":276986,"text":"give them permission to break\nthe will of the enemy,"},{"time":280000,"text":"to prepare them for interrogation,\nto soften them up,"},{"time":282501,"text":"to take the gloves off."},{"time":283751,"text":"Those are the euphemisms,\nand this is how it was interpreted."},{"time":287634,"text":"Let's go down to that dungeon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291285,"text":"(Typewriting)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293079,"text":"[Abu Ghraib Iraq Prison Abuses 2008\nMilitary Police Guards' Photos]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":299088,"text":"[The following images include nudity\nand graphic depictions of violence]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":306178,"text":"(Camera shutter sounds)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":327013,"text":"(Thuds)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":333561,"text":"(Camera shutter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":347356,"text":"(Camera shutter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":357000,"text":"(Breathing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"(Bells)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":395059,"text":"(Bells end)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":397079,"text":"So, pretty horrific."},{"time":399341,"text":"That's one of the visual\nillustrations of evil."},{"time":403172,"text":"And it should not have escaped you"},{"time":404957,"text":"that the reason I paired\nthe prisoner with his arms out"},{"time":408218,"text":"with Leonardo da Vinci's ode to humanity"},{"time":411000,"text":"is that that prisoner was mentally ill."},{"time":413606,"text":"That prisoner covered himself\nwith shit every day,"},{"time":415983,"text":"they had to roll him in dirt\nso he wouldn't stink."},{"time":418425,"text":"But the guards ended up\ncalling him \"Shit Boy.\""},{"time":420797,"text":"What was he doing in that prison\nrather than in some mental institution?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":425497,"text":"In any event, here's former\nSecretary of Defense Rumsfeld."},{"time":428236,"text":"He comes down and says,\n\"I want to know, who is responsible?"},{"time":431070,"text":"Who are the bad apples?\""},{"time":432473,"text":"Well, that's a bad question."},{"time":433905,"text":"You have to reframe it and ask,\n\"What is responsible?\""},{"time":436550,"text":"\"What\" could be the who of people,"},{"time":438222,"text":"but it could also be\nthe what of the situation,"},{"time":440783,"text":"and obviously that's wrongheaded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442493,"text":"How do psychologists try to understand\nsuch transformations of human character,"},{"time":446362,"text":"if you believe\nthat they were good soldiers"},{"time":448386,"text":"before they went down to that dungeon?"},{"time":450220,"text":"There are three ways.\nThe main way is called dispositional."},{"time":453106,"text":"We look at what's inside\nof the person, the bad apples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"This is the foundation\nof all of social science,"},{"time":459335,"text":"the foundation of religion,\nthe foundation of war."},{"time":463000,"text":"Social psychologists like me\ncome along and say,"},{"time":465263,"text":"\"Yeah, people are the actors on the stage,"},{"time":467406,"text":"but you'll have to be aware\nof the situation."},{"time":469780,"text":"Who are the cast of characters?\nWhat's the costume?"},{"time":472185,"text":"Is there a stage director?\""},{"time":473668,"text":"And so we're interested in\nwhat are the external factors"},{"time":476359,"text":"around the individual -- the bad barrel?"},{"time":478904,"text":"Social scientists stop there\nand they miss the big point"},{"time":481575,"text":"that I discovered when I became\nan expert witness for Abu Ghraib."},{"time":484838,"text":"The power is in the system."},{"time":486413,"text":"The system creates the situation\nthat corrupts the individuals,"},{"time":489678,"text":"and the system is the legal, political,\neconomic, cultural background."},{"time":494486,"text":"And this is where the power\nis of the bad-barrel makers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498139,"text":"If you want to change a person,\nchange the situation."},{"time":500664,"text":"And to change it, you've got to know\nwhere the power is, in the system."},{"time":504077,"text":"So the Lucifer effect\ninvolves understanding"},{"time":506149,"text":"human character transformations\nwith these three factors."},{"time":511124,"text":"And it's a dynamic interplay."},{"time":512537,"text":"What do the people bring\ninto the situation?"},{"time":514627,"text":"What does the situation bring out of them?"},{"time":516659,"text":"And what is the system\nthat creates and maintains that situation?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":520624,"text":"My recent book,\n\"The Lucifer Effect,\" is about,"},{"time":522932,"text":"how do you understand\nhow good people turn evil?"},{"time":525195,"text":"And it has a lot of detail\nabout what I'm going to talk about today."},{"time":528896,"text":"So Dr. Z's \"Lucifer Effect,\"\nalthough it focuses on evil,"},{"time":532000,"text":"really is a celebration of the human\nmind's infinite capacity"},{"time":536184,"text":"to make any of us kind or cruel,"},{"time":538766,"text":"caring or indifferent,\ncreative or destructive,"},{"time":541312,"text":"and it makes some of us villains."},{"time":543614,"text":"And the good news that I'm going\nto hopefully come to at the end"},{"time":546735,"text":"is that it makes some of us heroes."},{"time":549651,"text":"This wonderful cartoon in the New Yorker\nsummarizes my whole talk:"},{"time":553224,"text":"\"I'm neither a good cop\nnor a bad cop, Jerome."},{"time":555391,"text":"Like yourself, I'm a complex amalgam"},{"time":557374,"text":"of positive and negative\npersonality traits"},{"time":559867,"text":"that emerge or not, depending\non the circumstances.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":563381,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":565390,"text":"There's a study some of you\nthink you know about,"},{"time":568266,"text":"but very few people\nhave ever read the story."},{"time":570477,"text":"You watched the movie."},{"time":572426,"text":"This is Stanley Milgram,\nlittle Jewish kid from the Bronx,"},{"time":575799,"text":"and he asked the question,\n\"Could the Holocaust happen here, now?\""},{"time":578922,"text":"People say, \"No, that's Nazi Germany,\nHitler, you know, that's 1939.\""},{"time":582451,"text":"He said, \"Yeah, but suppose\nHitler asked you,"},{"time":584868,"text":"'Would you electrocute a stranger?'\n'No way, I'm a good person.'\""},{"time":588062,"text":"He said, \"Why don't\nwe put you in a situation"},{"time":590182,"text":"and give you a chance\nto see what you would do?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":592445,"text":"And so what he did was he tested\n1,000 ordinary people."},{"time":595554,"text":"500 New Haven, Connecticut,\n500 Bridgeport."},{"time":599645,"text":"And the ad said, \"Psychologists\nwant to understand memory."},{"time":602384,"text":"We want to improve people's memory,\nbecause it is the key to success.\""},{"time":605702,"text":"OK?"},{"time":607904,"text":"\"We're going to give you five bucks --\nfour dollars for your time."},{"time":611913,"text":"We don't want college students.\nWe want men between 20 and 50.\""},{"time":615391,"text":"In the later studies, they ran women."},{"time":617177,"text":"Ordinary people: barbers,\nclerks, white-collar people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620274,"text":"So, you go down,"},{"time":621878,"text":"one of you will be a learner,\none will be a teacher."},{"time":624413,"text":"The learner's a genial, middle-aged guy."},{"time":626342,"text":"He gets tied up to the shock\napparatus in another room."},{"time":629475,"text":"The learner could be middle-aged,\ncould be as young as 20."},{"time":633067,"text":"And one of you is told by the authority,\nthe guy in the lab coat,"},{"time":636307,"text":"\"Your job as teacher is to give him\nmaterial to learn."},{"time":638946,"text":"Gets it right, reward."},{"time":640184,"text":"Gets it wrong, you press\na button on the shock box."},{"time":642599,"text":"The first button is 15 volts.\nHe doesn't even feel it.\""},{"time":646000,"text":"That's the key."},{"time":647187,"text":"All evil starts with 15 volts."},{"time":649000,"text":"And then the next step\nis another 15 volts."},{"time":651849,"text":"The problem is, at the end\nof the line, it's 450 volts."},{"time":654870,"text":"And as you go along, the guy is screaming,"},{"time":657000,"text":"\"I've got a heart condition!\nI'm out of here!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":659215,"text":"You're a good person. You complain."},{"time":660945,"text":"\"Sir, who will be responsible\nif something happens to him?\""},{"time":663825,"text":"The experimenter says,\n\"Don't worry, I will be responsible."},{"time":666612,"text":"Continue, teacher.\""},{"time":667965,"text":"And the question is, who would go\nall the way to 450 volts?"},{"time":671794,"text":"You should notice here,\nwhen it gets up to 375,"},{"time":674394,"text":"it says, \"Danger. Severe Shock.\""},{"time":675943,"text":"When it gets up to here, there's \"XXX\" --\nthe pornography of power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679737,"text":"So Milgram asks 40 psychiatrists,"},{"time":681871,"text":"\"What percent of American citizens\nwould go to the end?\""},{"time":685000,"text":"They said only one percent."},{"time":686525,"text":"Because that's sadistic behavior,\nand we know, psychiatry knows,"},{"time":690115,"text":"only one percent\nof Americans are sadistic."},{"time":692231,"text":"OK."},{"time":693987,"text":"Here's the data.\nThey could not be more wrong."},{"time":696617,"text":"Two thirds go all the way to 450 volts."},{"time":699462,"text":"This was just one study."},{"time":701000,"text":"Milgram did more than 16 studies."},{"time":703308,"text":"And look at this."},{"time":705331,"text":"In study 16, where you see\nsomebody like you go all the way,"},{"time":708192,"text":"90 percent go all the way."},{"time":710287,"text":"In study five, if you see people rebel,"},{"time":712499,"text":"90 percent rebel."},{"time":714612,"text":"What about women?\nStudy 13 -- no different than men."},{"time":717778,"text":"So Milgram is quantifying evil\nas the willingness of people"},{"time":721343,"text":"to blindly obey authority,\nto go all the way to 450 volts."},{"time":724446,"text":"And it's like a dial on human nature."},{"time":726592,"text":"A dial in a sense that you can make\nalmost everybody totally obedient,"},{"time":731000,"text":"down to the majority, down to none."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734607,"text":"What are the external parallels?\nFor all research is artificial."},{"time":737631,"text":"What's the validity in the real world?"},{"time":739465,"text":"912 American citizens\ncommitted suicide or were murdered"},{"time":742503,"text":"by family and friends\nin Guyana jungle in 1978,"},{"time":745512,"text":"because they were blindly obedient\nto this guy, their pastor --"},{"time":748566,"text":"not their priest -- their pastor,\nReverend Jim Jones."},{"time":751297,"text":"He persuaded them to commit mass suicide."},{"time":754117,"text":"And so, he's the modern Lucifer effect,"},{"time":756006,"text":"a man of God who becomes\nthe Angel of Death."},{"time":760502,"text":"Milgram's study is all about individual\nauthority to control people."},{"time":765633,"text":"Most of the time, we are in institutions,"},{"time":768000,"text":"so the Stanford Prison Study\nis a study of the power of institutions"},{"time":771561,"text":"to influence individual behavior."},{"time":773525,"text":"Interestingly, Stanley Milgram and I\nwere in the same high school class"},{"time":777153,"text":"in James Monroe in the Bronx, 1954."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780976,"text":"I did this study\nwith my graduate students,"},{"time":783087,"text":"especially Craig Haney --\nand it also began work with an ad."},{"time":785937,"text":"We had a cheap, little ad,"},{"time":787389,"text":"but we wanted college students\nfor a study of prison life."},{"time":791089,"text":"75 people volunteered,\ntook personality tests."},{"time":793553,"text":"We did interviews."},{"time":794827,"text":"Picked two dozen: the most normal,\nthe most healthy."},{"time":797297,"text":"Randomly assigned them\nto be prisoner and guard."},{"time":799588,"text":"So on day one, we knew we had good apples."},{"time":801632,"text":"I'm going to put them in a bad situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803609,"text":"And secondly, we know\nthere's no difference"},{"time":805910,"text":"between the boys who will be guards\nand those who will be prisoners."},{"time":809276,"text":"To the prisoners, we said,"},{"time":810826,"text":"\"Wait at home. The study\nwill begin Sunday.\""},{"time":812976,"text":"We didn't tell them"},{"time":814200,"text":"that the city police were going\nto come and do realistic arrests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817419,"text":"(Video) (Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":823839,"text":"[Day 1]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":851313,"text":"Student: A police car pulls up in front,\nand a cop comes to the front door,"},{"time":856311,"text":"and knocks, and says he's looking for me."},{"time":858330,"text":"So they, right there, you know,\nthey took me out the door,"},{"time":861275,"text":"they put my hands against the car."},{"time":864797,"text":"It was a real cop car,\nit was a real policeman,"},{"time":867022,"text":"and there were real\nneighbors in the street,"},{"time":869109,"text":"who didn't know\nthat this was an experiment."},{"time":872629,"text":"And there was cameras\nall around and neighbors all around."},{"time":875407,"text":"They put me in the car,\nthen they drove me around Palo Alto."},{"time":880178,"text":"They took me to the basement\nof the police station."},{"time":892213,"text":"Then they put me in a cell."},{"time":893631,"text":"I was the first one to be picked up,\nso they put me in a cell,"},{"time":896573,"text":"which was just like a room\nwith a door with bars on it."},{"time":900286,"text":"You could tell it wasn't a real jail."},{"time":902104,"text":"They locked me in there,\nin this degrading little outfit."},{"time":906610,"text":"They were taking\nthis experiment too seriously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909209,"text":"Here are the prisoners, who are going\nto be dehumanized, they'll become numbers."},{"time":913066,"text":"Here are the guards\nwith the symbols of power and anonymity."},{"time":915982,"text":"Guards get prisoners to clean the toilet\nbowls out with their bare hands,"},{"time":919455,"text":"to do other humiliating tasks."},{"time":920951,"text":"They strip them naked.\nThey sexually taunt them."},{"time":923217,"text":"They begin to do degrading activities,\nlike having them simulate sodomy."},{"time":926778,"text":"You saw simulating fellatio\nin soldiers in Abu Ghraib."},{"time":930033,"text":"My guards did it in five days."},{"time":932335,"text":"The stress reaction was so extreme"},{"time":934186,"text":"that normal kids we picked\nbecause they were healthy"},{"time":936646,"text":"had breakdowns within 36 hours."},{"time":938253,"text":"The study ended after six days,\nbecause it was out of control."},{"time":942302,"text":"Five kids had emotional breakdowns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946306,"text":"Does it make a difference"},{"time":947783,"text":"if warriors go to battle\nchanging their appearance or not?"},{"time":950532,"text":"If they're anonymous,\nhow do they treat their victims?"},{"time":953309,"text":"In some cultures, they go to war\nwithout changing their appearance."},{"time":956492,"text":"In others, they paint themselves\nlike \"Lord of the Flies.\""},{"time":959244,"text":"In some, they wear masks."},{"time":960460,"text":"In many, soldiers\nare anonymous in uniform."},{"time":962545,"text":"So this anthropologist, John Watson, found\n23 cultures that had two bits of data."},{"time":967266,"text":"Do they change their appearance? 15."},{"time":969629,"text":"Do they kill, torture, mutilate? 13."},{"time":972240,"text":"If they don't change their appearance,"},{"time":974087,"text":"only one of eight kills,\ntortures or mutilates."},{"time":976324,"text":"The key is in the red zone."},{"time":977652,"text":"If they change their appearance,"},{"time":979241,"text":"12 of 13 -- that's 90 percent --\nkill, torture, mutilate."},{"time":982976,"text":"And that's the power of anonymity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984620,"text":"So what are the seven social processes"},{"time":986549,"text":"that grease the slippery slope of evil?"},{"time":988431,"text":"Mindlessly taking the first small step."},{"time":990581,"text":"Dehumanization of others.\nDe-individuation of self."},{"time":993247,"text":"Diffusion of personal responsibility."},{"time":995173,"text":"Blind obedience to authority."},{"time":996844,"text":"Uncritical conformity to group norms."},{"time":998762,"text":"Passive tolerance of evil\nthrough inaction, or indifference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002000,"text":"And it happens when you're\nin a new or unfamiliar situation."},{"time":1004882,"text":"Your habitual response\npatterns don't work."},{"time":1006955,"text":"Your personality\nand morality are disengaged."},{"time":1010643,"text":"\"Nothing is easier\nthan to denounce the evildoer;"},{"time":1012977,"text":"nothing more difficult\nthan understanding him,\" Dostoyevsky."},{"time":1016023,"text":"Understanding is not excusing.\nPsychology is not excuse-ology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020059,"text":"So social and psychological\nresearch reveals"},{"time":1022210,"text":"how ordinary, good people can be\ntransformed without the drugs."},{"time":1025506,"text":"You don't need it. You just need\nthe social-psychological processes."},{"time":1028831,"text":"Real world parallels?"},{"time":1030550,"text":"Compare this with this."},{"time":1033976,"text":"James Schlesinger --\nI'm going to end with this -- says,"},{"time":1036688,"text":"\"Psychologists have attempted\nto understand how and why"},{"time":1039311,"text":"individuals and groups\nwho usually act humanely"},{"time":1041764,"text":"can sometimes act otherwise\nin certain circumstances.\""},{"time":1044976,"text":"That's the Lucifer effect."},{"time":1046239,"text":"And he goes on to say,\n\"The landmark Stanford study"},{"time":1048692,"text":"provides a cautionary tale\nfor all military operations.\""},{"time":1052636,"text":"If you give people power\nwithout oversight,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"it's a prescription for abuse."},{"time":1056507,"text":"They knew that, and let that happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059677,"text":"So another report, an investigative\nreport by General Fay,"},{"time":1062781,"text":"says the system is guilty."},{"time":1064755,"text":"In this report, he says it was\nthe environment that created Abu Ghraib,"},{"time":1068242,"text":"by leadership failures that contributed\nto the occurrence of such abuse,"},{"time":1071648,"text":"and because it remained undiscovered"},{"time":1073582,"text":"by higher authorities\nfor a long period of time."},{"time":1075846,"text":"Those abuses went on for three months."},{"time":1077695,"text":"Who was watching the store?"},{"time":1079327,"text":"The answer is nobody, I think on purpose."},{"time":1081598,"text":"He gave the guards permission\nto do those things,"},{"time":1083915,"text":"and they knew nobody was ever going\nto come down to that dungeon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087003,"text":"So you need a paradigm shift\nin all of these areas."},{"time":1089595,"text":"The shift is away from the medical model\nthat focuses only on the individual."},{"time":1093296,"text":"The shift is toward a public health model"},{"time":1096000,"text":"that recognizes situational\nand systemic vectors of disease."},{"time":1099806,"text":"Bullying is a disease.\nPrejudice is a disease."},{"time":1102167,"text":"Violence is a disease."},{"time":1103359,"text":"Since the Inquisition, we've been dealing\nwith problems at the individual level."},{"time":1107151,"text":"It doesn't work."},{"time":1108616,"text":"Aleksandr Solzhenitsyn says,\n\"The line between good and evil"},{"time":1111456,"text":"cuts through the heart\nof every human being.\""},{"time":1113600,"text":"That means that line is not out there."},{"time":1115436,"text":"That's a decision that you have\nto make, a personal thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1118431,"text":"So I want to end very quickly\non a positive note."},{"time":1121492,"text":"Heroism as the antidote to evil,"},{"time":1123976,"text":"by promoting the heroic imagination,"},{"time":1125895,"text":"especially in our kids,\nin our educational system."},{"time":1128417,"text":"We want kids to think,\n\"I'm a hero in waiting,"},{"time":1130905,"text":"waiting for the right\nsituation to come along,"},{"time":1133072,"text":"and I will act heroically."},{"time":1134639,"text":"My whole life, I'm now going\nto focus away from evil --"},{"time":1137341,"text":"that I've been in since I was a kid\n-- to understanding heroes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1140318,"text":"Banality of heroism."},{"time":1141507,"text":"It's ordinary people who do heroic deeds."},{"time":1143535,"text":"It's the counterpoint\nto Hannah Arendt's \"Banality of Evil.\""},{"time":1146505,"text":"Our traditional societal heroes are wrong,\nbecause they are the exceptions."},{"time":1150490,"text":"They organize their life around this.\nThat's why we know their names."},{"time":1153849,"text":"Our kids' heroes\nare also wrong models for them,"},{"time":1156151,"text":"because they have supernatural talents."},{"time":1158119,"text":"We want our kids to realize\nmost heroes are everyday people,"},{"time":1161104,"text":"and the heroic act is unusual."},{"time":1163232,"text":"This is Joe Darby."},{"time":1164547,"text":"He was the one that stopped\nthose abuses you saw,"},{"time":1166857,"text":"because when he saw those images,"},{"time":1168474,"text":"he turned them over\nto a senior investigating officer."},{"time":1171069,"text":"He was a low-level private,\nand that stopped it."},{"time":1173821,"text":"Was he a hero? No."},{"time":1175023,"text":"They had to put him in hiding,\nbecause people wanted to kill him,"},{"time":1178197,"text":"and then his mother and his wife."},{"time":1179873,"text":"For three years, they were in hiding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1181782,"text":"This is the woman who stopped\nthe Stanford Prison Study."},{"time":1184492,"text":"When I said it got out of control,\nI was the prison superintendent."},{"time":1187765,"text":"I didn't know it was out of control.\nI was totally indifferent."},{"time":1190788,"text":"She saw that madhouse and said,"},{"time":1192403,"text":"\"You know what, it's terrible\nwhat you're doing to those boys."},{"time":1195332,"text":"They're not prisoners nor guards,\nthey're boys, and you are responsible.\""},{"time":1199000,"text":"And I ended the study the next day."},{"time":1201539,"text":"The good news\nis I married her the next year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1203673,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1206000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1213445,"text":"I just came to my senses, obviously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1215480,"text":"So situations have the power\nto do [three things]."},{"time":1218173,"text":"But the point is,\nthis is the same situation"},{"time":1220978,"text":"that can inflame the hostile\nimagination in some of us,"},{"time":1224468,"text":"that makes us perpetrators of evil,"},{"time":1226229,"text":"can inspire the heroic\nimagination in others."},{"time":1228446,"text":"It's the same situation\nand you're on one side or the other."},{"time":1231584,"text":"Most people are guilty\nof the evil of inaction,"},{"time":1233799,"text":"because your mother said, \"Don't get\ninvolved. Mind your own business.\""},{"time":1237171,"text":"And you have to say,\n\"Mama, humanity is my business.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1239672,"text":"So the psychology of heroism is --\nwe're going to end in a moment --"},{"time":1242887,"text":"how do we encourage children\nin new hero courses,"},{"time":1245338,"text":"that I'm working on with Matt Langdon --\nhe has a hero workshop --"},{"time":1248654,"text":"to develop this heroic imagination,\nthis self-labeling,"},{"time":1251721,"text":"\"I am a hero in waiting,\"\nand teach them skills."},{"time":1254508,"text":"To be a hero, you have\nto learn to be a deviant,"},{"time":1256887,"text":"because you're always going\nagainst the conformity of the group."},{"time":1260537,"text":"Heroes are ordinary people whose social\nactions are extraordinary. Who act."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1264401,"text":"The key to heroism is two things."},{"time":1266176,"text":"You have to act\nwhen other people are passive."},{"time":1268581,"text":"B: You have to act socio-centrically,\nnot egocentrically."},{"time":1271372,"text":"And I want to end with a known story\nabout Wesley Autrey, New York subway hero."},{"time":1275179,"text":"Fifty-year-old African-American\nconstruction worker standing on a subway."},{"time":1279000,"text":"A white guy falls on the tracks."},{"time":1280552,"text":"The subway train is coming.\nThere's 75 people there."},{"time":1283036,"text":"You know what? They freeze."},{"time":1284556,"text":"He's got a reason not to get involved."},{"time":1286446,"text":"He's black, the guy's white,\nand he's got two kids."},{"time":1288887,"text":"Instead, he gives his kids to a stranger,"},{"time":1290864,"text":"jumps on the tracks,\nputs the guy between the tracks,"},{"time":1293365,"text":"lays on him, the subway goes over him."},{"time":1295559,"text":"Wesley and the guy --\n20 and a half inches height."},{"time":1298841,"text":"The train clearance is 21 inches."},{"time":1301680,"text":"A half an inch\nwould have taken his head off."},{"time":1304377,"text":"And he said, \"I did what anyone could do,\"\nno big deal to jump on the tracks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1308470,"text":"And the moral imperative\nis \"I did what everyone should do.\""},{"time":1312142,"text":"And so one day,\nyou will be in a new situation."},{"time":1315000,"text":"Take path one, you're going\nto be a perpetrator of evil."},{"time":1317644,"text":"Evil, meaning you're going to be\nArthur Andersen."},{"time":1320000,"text":"You're going to cheat,\nor you're going to allow bullying."},{"time":1322739,"text":"Path two, you become guilty\nof the evil of passive inaction."},{"time":1325577,"text":"Path three, you become a hero."},{"time":1327324,"text":"The point is, are we ready to take\nthe path to celebrating ordinary heroes,"},{"time":1331766,"text":"waiting for the right\nsituation to come along"},{"time":1333994,"text":"to put heroic imagination into action?"},{"time":1336084,"text":"Because it may only happen\nonce in your life,"},{"time":1338902,"text":"and when you pass it by,\nyou'll always know,"},{"time":1341069,"text":"I could have been a hero\nand I let it pass me by."},{"time":1343528,"text":"So the point is thinking it\nand then doing it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1346399,"text":"So I want to thank you. Thank you."},{"time":1348371,"text":"Let's oppose the power of evil systems\nat home and abroad,"},{"time":1351397,"text":"and let's focus on the positive."},{"time":1353000,"text":"Advocate for respect of personal dignity,\nfor justice and peace,"},{"time":1356545,"text":"which sadly our administration\nhas not been doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1358907,"text":"Thanks so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1360181,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}